rComments: very good professor, explains well and the notes are logical.
He is a great professor who really cares for his students.

Good lecturer, and incredibly helpful at office hours. He is always giving you little ways to help you out like intentionally giving you similar types of problems to the lectures and not making the calculus too difficult in questions. Also has a very good attitude and spends a lot of extra time just helping students.
Speaks very fast, rushes through a lot. He also barely posts on blackboard so you need to go to class to know details about the assignments and exams.
Verygood
Good professor who actually cares about his students. Quizzes and midterm are straightforward, but the final exam was the hardest exam I have ever written.

His lectures are very comprehensive and the notes you great from him are very structured and good to study from. The Midterm was good, but the final was the hardest thing I've ever done in my entire life, I swear I walked into a different course's exam.
very good!!
He does a great job explaining concepts and his lectures allow for great notes to be made. He has an accent so sit at the front but overall he is one of the bests profs I've ever had.
i hate math. i can't understand the prof. had an awful TA. go to tutorials, easy marks though.
Amazing accent which I don't remotely understand. Covers the last 5 chapters in the last two weeks. What a brilliant professor!

Mahinda was a great prof if you actually pay attention to his lectures and take notes. He gives hints about the exams during his lectures. The first half of the course was soft but after the midterm the work gets a bit tough but if you understand the concepts well you will do well. Make sure you ace the quizzes and practice by doing the webwork.
Mahinda was a great professor. Explained concept very clearly and took the time to make sure you understood everything in office hours.

He is the best professor I've had yet! He makes the material quite easy to understand and if you still don't get the material, he's there for you. This course wasn't hard at all. I suggest going to the lectures and doing textbook questions if needed. If you pay attention in class, you'll do well.

I highly recommend going to the lectures since it is not videotaped because he gives great examples which are the key to understanding the material. First half is pretty easy, second half gets confusing but if you go to class and office hours, he is really helpful. if you go to classes you don't even need the textbook.

Not a mathstats student so I had to sit in the front and away from friends to take in the work, Mahinda does a great job of explaining concepts and showing clear examples. Outside of class he's a really friendly, humble and helpful man, he's there for you and will go over his 2 hours of office hours just to make sure you understand the material.

He is such an amazing prof. When you asked for his help, he will literary stay longer than the listed office hours. Be prepare to spend 2 hours in his office hours. But that 2 hours is the best hours of your life. Mahinda rocks!!!

He is a very great and kind prof, just like your father. He marked our mid term by himself, so that he sacrificed his sleeping time, not only for letting students get back their exam paper as soon as possible, but also guarantee the equality for marking. He is a highly respectable prof, not just for his awesome inlustration of the course material!!

The prof had a heavy accent, but he covered everything that would show up on quizzes and exams. He is an easy stats prof, however the material gets boring and that's why ppl do worse on the final. midterm is 80+ guaranteed if u keep up and try. quizzes u can get almost perfect, final is a bit tougher cuz its cumulative, but if u study u can get 80
Nice prof, he treats students equally. Also, he teaches concepts clearly and notes were helpful. Easy midterm, hard exam.
best prof, very helpful

Great prof! Covers all the material in lecture, goes over examples well, answers questions, and sometimes he's really funny.  Tutorials are really easy, midterm was easy and final is a little tricky, but doable

quizzes and midterm are fine but final is quite hard!! Prof Samarakoon explains concepts well and did do some exam questions/ gives hints to midterm/exams during lectures.  try to practice as many past exams as possible b/c as you practice more and more you are building you confidences and starting the see some trends in finals!

He mumbles you can't understand what he's saying in class. It's like he's speaking an entirely different language. He goes way to fast and expects you to know everything when STAB22 is a beginner class. I know it's a part of "quantitative reasoning" but if you're not a math person... RUN if you have him as a prof. You pretty much learn from the txt
He is a great professor and a great human being.

Great prof, had him for STAB57. Really helpful and goes out of his way to help students. Explains concepts really well. You MUST ask questions in this course and show you care. Easy midterm, relatively hard final. Ended up with a good mark in the end.
Great Prof! Very helpful in office hours.
a truly genuine teacher!

Easy midterm, yet killer final. Do as many practice problems in the textbook as possible for a high grade. It's also beneficial to attend his lectures and note down example questions he presents as he'll probably test you on them later on. You're best bet would be to score really high on the midterm to maintain an A, otherwise good luck !
The best prof I have ever had.
Great Prof! If you see him one on one in office hours he is AWESOME! Explains everything and this guy is so soft spoken and a NICE GUY! I was so scared taking intro to stats, now i LOVE IT!
He's one of the best professors i've had. He see's the students at their level and makes asking questions less intimidating. extremely nice and helpful! BEST STATS PROFF!!
The best prof I've ever had! Explains concepts so clearly! He's very approachable, and is always willing to answer questions.
Amazing Professor. Super easy midterms, quizzes even easier, but final exam is brutal. Do the example final. I've never had a nicer professor so willing to help when needed!

i loved him! I got an 85% in this class (so happy) whereas I basically failed other math courses. He is so kind, clear, and makes his exams fair. No question is stupid in his class and not to mention he's so adorable!

He's funny but yet monotone. Midterm easy like high school test; but final is killer.  U can't study 4 da final cuz it's not related to da past finals or text Q's. U basically random guess w/o doing any calc. Quizes R easy. TA's are useless & boring. They dn't hlp w/ actually answering Q's. He made da crse pass-able & do-able!
excellent!!! best prof ever!

Prof. Samarakoon goes above and beyond. He teaches with heart and this course (however boring I thought it would be) turned out to be a lot of fun actually. Key is: ALWAYS ask questions. Never go home not knowing something and ALWAYS read ahead! And do his final exam past paper! You'll do great.

i had him for three semesters straight (that's one full year) and like everyone said, everything's easy except for the final exam. my advice is to make sure you do the sample exams and  dont be scared to go to his office hours if you need help and im sure you'll be okay. i ended up have three As in the three courses that he was teaching.
amazing prof, always there to help, midterm was easy, but the final definitely kills you
Do not slack after you ace the midterm, which you will, guaranteed.
MIDTERM AND QUIZZES ARE EASY. BUT FINAL IS REALLY HARD
The course was easy except for the final.  The prof was really friendly, and was extremely fair in all of his grading.

the prof is amazing! so basically the midterm was a joke...but the FINAL IS KILLER!!! i literally guessed every question but 3 out of 30. i was soo scared i was gonna get like 50 something...but they bell curve like crazy and u get really surprised when u see ur mark! it made my life when i saw what i got in the course...

oh man, i was breezing this course till the final. so killer, my advice make sure ur truly ready for the final go over the practice exam, ask question, don't think that just because you're doing good the final will be the same cause ur wrong. but he's a good prof, make stat easy.(and i'm not a math person)

As many people already said, everything before the final was easy peasy. The BEST way to prepare for his final was to go into the professor's hours during the weeks before exams and go over the practice final over with him. Another way is to make friends.  That's how I got 2 additional copies of other final exams to study from (tottaly legit).

Man this class was JOKE until the Final. I mean seriously he didn't even care if the class was getting a 90% class avg. he knew that he was going to kill us all in the final. His Midterm was a joke, so are his quizes. Was going with 92% to the final exam which was 50% and I ended up with 73% overal. The exam was the hardest exam I ever faced!
